title: Data Science Utility Functions
text: flextable package versatile exactly looking get nicely formatted tables directly R(studio) Word. holds true datscience::format_flextable() function datscience package. just applies repetitive formatting necessary convert flextable “publication ready” APA formatted table. One example flexibility just try print factor loadings prinicipal component analysis (PCA, psych::prinicial) Let’s first create exemplary PCA[1, 2]extract factor loadings: (also conveniently packaged function apa_factorLoadings() function) Formatting loadings APA just one function: FLFF.png
code: # Creation of an Example Prinicipal Component Analysis pacman::p_load(psych, dplyr) pc <- principal(Harman74.cor$cov, 4, rotate = "varimax") pc_loadings <- pc %>%   fa.sort() %>%   .[["loadings"]] %>%   round(3) %>%   unclass() %>%   as.data.frame() %>%   mutate(across(     everything(),     ~ if_else((. < 0.3), "", as.character(.))   )) %>%    bind_cols(Communality = pc$communality,             Uniqueness = pc$uniquenesses,             Complexity = pc$complexity) %>%    mutate(across(where(is.numeric),round, 2)) %>%    tibble::rownames_to_column("items") formatted_loadings <- datscience::format_flextable(flextable::flextable(pc_loadings),                                                    table_caption = c("Table 3","Factor Loadings in Exemplary PCA")) formatted_loadings

title: Create APA Publication Ready Correlation Table and Export to Word or Powerpoint — apa_corrTable
text: df Data.frame, mandatory argument. Consider filtering passing e.g. dplyr::select() dplyr::filter() summarystats vector summary stats included bottom correlation. Default c("mean","sd") Options one c("mean","sd","median","range","min","max","skew", "kurtosis","se"). NA given, summarystats added. method Type correlation. Options currently: "pearson", "spearman" "polychoric" rmDiag diagonal corr matrix kept (FALSE) removed (TRUE) sig.level many stars per level significance, options include .05 .01 .001 nod (Optional) Integer Integer Vector. Number Decimals. case -1 simple convention based sample size applied determination number decimal points. See ?datscience::get_number_of_decimals. can also provide Integer vector, want different number decimals correlations summary stats. first integer determines nod correlations, second summary stats. E.g., c(2,-1) give 2 decimals correlations apply convention summary stats. Default nod = c(2,-1).  See get_number_of_decimals ?datscience::get_number_of_decimals filepath (Optional) Path filename APA ready table saved, options include common filetypes .docx (Word), .pptx (Powerpoint), .html (Webpage). Default filepath = NA. NA given, file saved. overwrite (Optional) Boolean, default FALSE. overwrite FALSE files already exists, serialized version filename created (.e., appending _001, _002). Utilizes serialNext ... (Optional), Additional arguments can passed format_flextable (e.g., fontsize, font ...) serialNext
